<SUMMARY>
SUMMARY:

 This document proposes to revise an earlier 
proposed airworthiness directive (AD), which would have 
superseded AD 91-08-01. That AD currently requires the 
following on Jetstream Aircraft Limited (JAL) Jetstream 
Model 3101 airplanes: revising the maximum speed for 
flaps at 50 degrees from 153/149 knots indicated 
airspeed (KIAS) to 130 KIAS; and limiting the maximum 
flap extension to 20 degrees anytime ice is present on 
the airplane. The previous notice proposed to provide 
the option of incorporating a flap system modification 
that would eliminate the requirements of AD 91-08-01. 
Since publication of that proposal, the Federal 
Aviation Administration (FAA) has re-examined all 
information related to this subject, and has determined 
that the flap system modification should be made 
mandatory rather than optional. The proposed actions 
are intended to prevent sudden pitch down of the 
airplane during icing conditions, which could lead to 
loss of control of the airplane. 


